    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but it feels like the \"pro-density\" crowd usually just dismisses those concerns by saying \"supply will eventually lower prices\" or whatever. honestly, it feels like they're just pushing a specific agenda to favor developers. is there actually any real evidence that high-density zoning helps the working class, or is it just an urbanist talking point?",
